race.comment: DUSHENKA (2) looked handy winning around this circuit on debut before not measuring up in Group 2 company at Randwick before the spell. Has been thereabouts in both runs since the break and will be ready to peak now third-up. Should be right there at the business end. SEVILO (7) is still a maiden but has been well in the betting in both starts to date and where there's smoke there's fire. Can improve enough to take this out. CONTINGENCY (1) hasn't done much wrong stringing back-to-back victories to start the career, albeit in lesser grade. Hard to ignore winning form. DIVERSITY (8) will be high on confidence following that last-start Doomben victory and gets in well at the weights with the 3kg claim. Include in calculations. CASTELLO GRANDE (4) next in line from the Heathcote barn.
